# QA / UX Gates

Enforcement rules for role routing and documentation sync on Web UI changes. Full context: `AGENT.md` AI roles, `CURSOR.md`, skill files under `.ai/skills/`.

## Role routing

| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| DNS/MTR/metrics/core API | `.ai/skills/dns-debug/SKILL.md` |
| Dashboard IA, states, filters, chart hierarchy, microcopy | `.ai/skills/ux-designer/SKILL.md` |
| Acceptance, regression, API↔UI correctness, compare deltas | `.ai/skills/qa-ui/SKILL.md` |

**Large UI change:** UX designer → implement → Stage 1 self-check → UX audit → QA validate → fix pass → release readiness.

**Pre-release workflow:** Stages 1–3 required for all visual/behavioral UI changes. See `AGENT.md` → Pre-release UX workflow.

**Compare mode:** apply **both** `qa-ui` and `ux-designer` skills; update `debugging-checklist.md`.

## Gates (task incomplete until satisfied)

1. **Major UI feature** — QA acceptance perspective (`qa-ui` skill checklist)
2. **Major UX / IA change** — UX designer perspective (`ux-designer` skill)
3. **New dashboard section** — UX clarity: purpose, states, microcopy documented
4. **Historical mode** — QA checklist: retention, stale, empty states, truncation honesty
5. **Compare mode** — both skills; server-side delta verification; color semantics for improvement vs regression
6. **Visual changes** — state coverage: loading, empty, error, stale, retention exceeded, no EDNS, no MTR
7. **History features** — retention/empty-state design (UX); never imply full history from event buffer alone (QA)
8. **Live UX v2** — `global_status` rollup, KPI poll trends, auto-refresh toggle, 3-tier IA sub-nav documented in `ux-designer` + `debugging-checklist.md` § Live UX
9. **UX audit required** — Stage 2 pre-release UX audit deliverable (`ux-designer` skill) before QA release readiness
10. **Responsive review** — QA responsive width checklist at 8 widths (1920–375px); laptop breakage = P1 blocker
11. **Chart/layout QA** — chart readability, 3-tier layout hierarchy, filter bar at laptop widths (`qa-ui` skill)
12. **No critical UX defects** — no open P0/P1 UX or observability findings at release
13. **No broken laptop/tablet** — core triage flow intact at 1024–1440px and 768px
14. **State design + docs sync** — loading/empty/error/stale/retention on changed panels; pre-release workflow sections synced in skills, `AGENT.md`, `debugging-checklist.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `CURSOR.md`, rules
15. **i18n completeness** — new UI strings in EN + RU; no raw translation keys in UI; Historical/Compare fully localized; RU responsive check at laptop widths
16. **Release documentation** — `CHANGELOG.md` + `docs/releases/X.Y.Z.md` updated; version in `app/main.py` synced; release summary lists UX, responsive, localization, and docs changes
17. **PostgreSQL retention** — history/compare features must respect `DNS_DEBUG_DB_RETENTION_DAYS`; no feature ships without retention messaging when DB enabled

## Prohibited without gates

- Shipping compare mode without delta tests or QA cross-check against `/api/ui/compare`
- Visual UI changes without loading/empty/error state coverage
- Historical views without retention/truncation messaging
- Treating cache heuristic as real Docker DNS cache in UI copy
- Breaking additive JSON contracts on `/api/ui/*` without explicit approval
- Shipping UI changes without Stage 2 UX audit and Stage 3 QA release readiness
- Releasing with open P1 responsive laptop/tablet breakage on core triage flow
- Shipping UI/UX/i18n/workflow changes without `CHANGELOG.md` and `docs/releases/X.Y.Z.md` update
- Shipping UI changes without EN + RU translation keys for new user-facing strings
- Marking UI work complete with partial RU localization or raw `signals.*` keys visible
- Marking a release complete with version mismatch between `app/main.py` and CHANGELOG

## Doc sync (same change as code)

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| Charts, filters, view modes, historical/compare | `qa-ui` + `ux-designer`, `debugging-checklist.md`, `AGENT.md` |
| Dashboard IA or states | `ux-designer`, `AGENT.md` UI section |
| New UI endpoints or envelope fields | `AGENT.md`, `debugging-checklist.md`, `qa-ui` |
| New env var | `AGENT.md`, `dns-debug` skill, `CLAUDE.md`, `CURSOR.md`, `dns-debug-project.mdc` |
| UI/UX/i18n/workflow release | `CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/releases/X.Y.Z.md`, version in `app/main.py`, AI docs |

Routing is centralized in `AGENT.md` + `CURSOR.md` — do not create duplicate `AGENTS.md`.
